Recall's hash-based content identity, reduced extraction provenance, and
stage-oriented retry design are independent adaptations informed by these
upstream source paths:

- `panoptikon/src/jobs/files.rs` — content identity and path reconciliation.
- `panoptikon/src/db/extraction_write.rs` — atomic extraction/provenance
  records.
- `panoptikon/src/jobs/extraction.rs` — extraction lifecycle and completion
  boundaries.
- `panoptikon/src/pql/embedding_utils.rs` — typed/versioned vector-storage
  concepts (not copied; sqlite-vec is not bundled in this POC).
- `panoptikon/src/inferio/registry.rs`, `manager.rs`, and `worker.rs` — model
  manifest/lifecycle concepts only.
- `docs/inferio-worker-protocol.md` — future worker-boundary reference only.

No Panoptikon HTTP server, PQL API, desktop-server supervisor, Python setup
machinery, browser UI, or Python worker code is included in Recall.

Modifications in Recall: the concepts above were reduced to local, in-process
Tauri/Rust and SQLite workflows.  Recall does not require a Python runtime.
